Class SoapClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.swatt.soap.SoapClient

  • public class SoapClient
extends java.lang.Object
    Use this client to send Soap messages to an API.

    Note: This class uses SOAP version 1.1 protocols.

      • SoapClient

        public SoapClient(java.lang.String _url,
                  java.lang.String _user,
                  java.lang.String _pass)
        Creates this Soap client for use against a given endpoint, with basic authentication.
        Parameters:
        _url - The full URL of the API endpoint that this client will be hitting.
        _user - The username to use for authentication, or null to ignore.
        _pass - The password to use for authentication, or null to ignore.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given URL endpoint is not in a valid URL format.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If either the given Username or Password are null but not both.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If either the given Username or Password are blank strings.
        java.lang.RuntimeException - If a MessageFactory could not be created.
